value.value: An artery that supplies blood to the index finger, either the radial artery of the index finger or the ulnar proper digital artery.
An artery that supplies blood to the little finger, either the ulnar or radial proper digital artery.
An artery that supplies blood to the middle finger, either the ulnar or radial proper digital artery.
An artery that supplies blood to the ring finger, either the ulnar or radial proper digital artery.
A member of the tyrphostin family of tyrosine kinase inhibitors, that selectively inhibits epidermal growth factor receptor kinase activity. (NCI)

label.value: Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor Superfamily Member 1A

value.value: Tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 1A (455 aa, ~50 kDa) is encoded by the human TNFRSF1A gene. This protein is involved in tumor necrosis factor signaling and the initiation of apoptosis.
An artery that supplies blood to the thumb; either the ulnopalmar, radiopalmar, ulnodorsal, or radiodorsal digital artery to the thumb, or the princeps pollicis artery.

The segment of the gastrointestinal tract where the terminal ileum transitions to the cecum, and where the ileocecal sphincter regulates the movement of chyme from the small intestine into the large intestine.
The region of the body that comprises the uterine cervix and vagina.
The region of the body surrounding the urinary bladder.
Diagnosis based on a pathological assessment.
The determination of the amount of SARS-CoV-2 nucleocapsid protein antibody in a sample.
The determination of the amount of SARS-CoV-2 spike protein antibody in a sample.
The determination of the amount of Human Coronavirus 229E in a sample.
The determination of the amount of Human Coronavirus HKU1 in a sample.
The determination of the amount of Human Coronavirus NL63 in a sample.
DNA topoisomerase 2-alpha (1531 aa, ~174 kDa) is encoded by the human TOP2A gene. This protein is involved in the modulation of DNA topology.
The determination of the amount of Human Coronavirus OC43 in a sample.
The determination of the amount of Human Metapneumovirus in a sample.
The determination of the amount of Human Parainfluenza Virus 2 in a sample.
The determination of the amount of Human Parainfluenza Virus 3 in a sample.
The determination of the amount of Human Parainfluenza Virus 4 in a sample.
The determination of the amount of Bordetella parapertussis in a sample.
The determination of the amount of Chlamydia pneumoniae in a sample.
A measurement of the mass of all skeletal muscle in the body.
A measurement of the mass of the muscles of the arms and legs.

An alphacoronavirus, first isolated in 1966, that is believed to have originated from African hipposiderid bats and utilizes aminopeptidase N as its major receptor. It is associated with respiratory infections in humans, particularly the common cold, and may have neuroinvasive properties.
DNA topoisomerase 2-beta (1626 aa, ~183 kDa) is encoded by the human TOP2B gene. This protein plays a role in DNA relaxation.

A betacoronavirus, first isolated in 2005, that utilizes 9-O-acetylated sialic acid as a receptor determinant and has hemagglutinin-esterase activity. It is associated with human respiratory infections, particularly the common cold, and febrile seizures.

An alphacoronavirus, first isolated in 2004, that utilizes angiotensin-converting enzyme-2 as its major receptor and is associated with respiratory infections in humans, particularly the common cold and croup.

A betacoronavirus, first isolated in 1967, that utilizes 9-O-acetylated sialic acid as a receptor determinant and has hemagglutinin-esterase activity. It is associated with respiratory infections in humans, particularly the common cold, and may have neuroinvasive properties.
A type of functional MRI that images dynamic changes in brain tissue while the subject performs a task or experiences a sensory stimulus designed to target specific cognitive processes.
A type of functional magnetic resonance imaging that is performed on an organ or brain tissue in the absence of a stimulus or task.

A chemical titration method described by van de Kamer, et al. in 1949 in which fecal fat is quantitatively measured by conversion of fecal lipids into fatty acids through saponification with ethanolic potassium hydroxide, release of the free fatty acids by the addition of hydrochloric acid and extraction into ether, and titration of the fatty acids against sodium hydroxide.

label.value: Intracellular Cytokine Stain Flow Cytometric Assay

value.value: A technique that is used with flow cytometry to measure cytokine production in isolated cells. Cells are stimulated with an antigen or mitogen, and cytokine secretion is blocked using protein transport inhibitors. The cells are then stained with fluorochrome labeled monoclonal antibodies that target surface markers, fixed and permeabilized, and stained with fluorochrome labeled anti-cytokine monoclonal antibodies prior to analysis by flow cytometry.
A type of electrochemiluminescence assay that utilizes primary and secondary antibodies in a two-step binding process.

A type of ELISA assay that uses a reference antigen to competitively bind labeled antibody against an antigen of interest. The strength of the signal interference caused by antibody bound to the reference antigen is used to determine the concentration of the antigen of interest.
The evaluation of oneself or one's actions or performance without external input.
CREB-binding protein (2442 aa, ~265 kDa) is encoded by the human CREBBP gene. This protein is involved in the mediation of histone acetylation.
An immunoassay that utilizes the interactions between two molecules, or the binding of molecules to antibodies, to detect and quantify analytes of interest.

An immunoassay where results can be generated immediately or within minutes from antibody/antigen interactions with an analyte of interest in a biological specimen with little or no sample processing.

A standardized set of ten equivalent paragraphs of text, based on everyday life reading demands with equivalent levels of difficulty, that is used to provide repeat assessments of reading performance for a wide range of subjects. It is available in multiple languages.

A score originally developed by D'Haens et al. (1998) and assigned based on the histologic evaluation of acute and chronic inflammatory changes, epithelial damage, and the extent of inflammation in Crohn's disease mucosal biopsy specimens, according to the Global Histologic Disease Activity Score. (G R D'Haens, K Geboes, M Peeters, F Baert, F Penninckx, P Rutgeerts. Early lesions of recurrent Crohn's disease caused by infusion of intestinal contents in excluded ileum. Gastroenterology. 1998 Feb;114(2):262-7).

A score developed by Mosli et al. (2017) and assigned based on the histologic evaluation of disease activity in ulcerative colitis. (Mahmoud H Mosli, Brian G Feagan, Guangyong Zou, et al. Development and validation of a histological index for UC. Gut. 2017 Jan;66(1):50-58.)

label.value: Intraepithelial Lymphocytes to Enterocytes Ratio Measurement

value.value: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the lymphocytes to enterocytes within the epithelium of a biological specimen.
An evaluation of the presence or degree of epithelial damage present in a sample.
An evaluation of the presence or degree of tissue architectural changes present in a sample.

label.value: Infiltration of Mononuclear Cells in Lamina Propria Assessment

value.value: An evaluation of the presence or degree of infiltration of mononuclear cells into the lamina propria present in a sample.

label.value: Infiltration of Polymorphonuclear Cells in Lamina Propria Assessment

value.value: An evaluation of the presence or degree of infiltration of polymorphonuclear cells into the lamina propria present in a sample.
Histone acetyltransferase p300 (2414 aa, ~264 kDa) is encoded by the human EP300 gene. This protein is involved in histone acetylation, transcriptional regulation and development.
